{
  "texts": [
    "The CSS1 and CSS2 correlations are generated to assess the CSS values' stability further.",
    "The correlations are close to zero (Pearson correlation = 0.075), showing that the substantial association is attributable to CSS's resiliency in real-world pharmaceutical combinations.",
    "There was a strong association between the CSS value and the values produced from individual replicates (minimum Pearson correlation = 0.97).",
    "Because the CSS1 and CSS2 values in the medicine combination sensitivity score are often constant, averaging them as a summary for the medicine combination sensitivity score is recommended.",
    "The O'Neil dataset's numerical variable correlation is shown in Fig. 3."
  ]
}